HEADWORD: Amazonian
<hw>Am`a*zo"ni*an</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Pertaining to or resembling an Amazon; of masculine manners;
warlike.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the river Amazon in South
America, or to its valley.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amazon stone</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Amazonite</ent>⟦br⟧
